node.text: Next up on Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) visits One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) in beautiful Riviera Nayarit, Mexico, where Mixologist Ivan Aguilar shows us how to make one of his favorite cocktails. Of course, no trip to Mexico is complete without tequila, so naturally, that’s our spirit of choice for this episode. In fact, Ivan shows us that tequila can be used to add a twist to cocktails that traditionally use other liquors. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Calling All Tequila Lovers, This Cocktail Could Become Your New Favorite

node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Elevate Your Next Summer Get-together With These Cocktail Recipes

node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. On this episode, Sean visits @themarkhotelny, where Bartender Ken Ziegler shows us how to make a ginger margarita — a fresh take on the classic. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Learn How One of the Best Hotels in NYC Makes Its Signature Margarita

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! Tour by @_thebluewalk

node.title: This Greek Island Has All of the Beauty and None of the Crowds

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Underground Railroad Tour of Alexandria, Virginia. We’ll hear stories as recorded by William Still, an abolitionist based in Philadelphia, where many enslaved people fled to from Alexandria. These stories will give insight into the historic work of the Underground Railroad and the experiences of the individuals who traveled it in hopes of escaping slavery. Come along. Tour by @manumissiontour

node.title: Join Us on the Underground Railroad Tour of Alexandria, Virginia

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Holiday Tour of New York City. This year, however, most of those visitors will be staying home, which is why we decided to bring New York City’s holiday cheer to you. Join us as we visit the Rockefeller Christmas Tree, Radio City Music Hall, and more. Happy holidays! Tour by @topdogtoursnyc

node.text:
This week on Behind the Views: Paul Fuentes (@paulfuentes_photo). Paul’s journey with photography started the “opposite” of most photographers, he says. Before he ever got behind the lens, he first developed an interest in graphic design and editing. “I mastered different photo editing tools like Photoshop and Lightroom, and then getting behind the lens came as a necessity to complement my future work.”
.
When asked about his approach to shooting: “I work with multi-layer images, so I’m always searching for many different elements to layer together to create a final shot. I seek out bright lighting, contrast shadows, symmetry, soft colors, and vintage architecture.” 
.
His advice for aspiring photographers: “Tell a story with your photos. It's not all about taking photos of glamorous places. But telling a story takes patience, and waiting for the right conditions can takes hours. I usually visit a location first to familiarize myself with it and come back later to shoot when it’s less crowded.” 
.
In Paul’s go-to camera bag you’ll find Hasselblad X1D II and Nikon D850 cameras, 24-70mm and 35-75mm lenses, memory cards, and a Manfrotto 055 Tripod.
.
All photos by @paulfuentes_photo

node.text: Next up on Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) visits One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) in beautiful Riviera Nayarit, Mexico, where Mixologist Ivan Aguilar shows us how to make one of his favorite cocktails. Of course, no trip to Mexico is complete without tequila, so naturally, that’s our spirit of choice for this episode. In fact, Ivan shows us that tequila can be used to add a twist to cocktails that traditionally use other liquors. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!
